@EndNode

@Node KewlChat "KewlChat - The best 2 modem link chatting program"

 @{b}KewlChat@{ub} is one of my favourite programs as it allows 2 friends
to connect there modem to each other and talk it's easy to use and
in the registered version no modem commands have to be typed in.
  KewlChat is the only program i have wrote that has to be registered
for the full version but i think it's worth it when you see what you
get.
  If you would like to see a DEMO version first please send Ł1.00 on
an ENGLISH cheque or in ENGLISH cash, i will NOT except anything else
please make the cheque payable to Chris Seward.
  Or you could always go stright ahead and get the FULL version at a
bargin price of Ł2.00 i will still only accept ENGLISH money and
ENGLISH cheques for the full version.
  Please send your money to the address in the @{"Contact" link Contact} bit. Or you
could email for the info pack about KewlChat.

                            @{"Main Menu" link Main}

@Endnode

@Node BackChat "BackChat - Swear shout and take all you anger out on this program"

 @{b}BackChat@{ub} is a classic program, quite a few have been done and here's
another one, well your wondering, What is it? well it's an Eliza style
program where you type something in and it answers back with a funny reply
i can't tell you what version i'm up to because it gets updated to much.
For the latest version send a disk with a stamp to my addess which can be
found in the @{"Contact" link Contact} section of this guide. Or you can always email
me at Nicron@Jinxster.demon.co.uk

                            @{"Main Menu" link Main}

@Endnode

@Node KeyBoard "Kee-Bored - A great little keyboard"

 @{b}Kee-Bored@{ub} is the latest program i have wrote but NOT the best, it's a
little key-board with three built in tunes two drum type pads and over 15
keys, the keys don't have proper key board sounds and you don't get the
write letters either but it's good to mess around with. If you want this
program just send 1 disk and a stamp to my address which can be found in
the @{"Contact" link Contact} section of this guide. Or you can email me at Nicron@Jinxster.demon.co.uk

                            @{"Main Menu" link Main}

@Endnode

@Node Author "Author - About Chris Seward"

 Chris Seward (Me) is the only member of Nicron Productions he does
all the work and makes all the programs i wouldn't mind more members
so if anyone wants to join just @{"Contact" link Contact} me and i'll sort something
out with you. I am 13 years old but don't let that put you off, no-one
else seems to do anything for the amiga so i will :) I will always stick
with the amiga even if no-one else will, i belive good programs at low
prices will save the amiga. All my programs are written in amos, ATM, but
i am hoping to start writting programs for the palmtop computer the Psion
if anyone wants any info contact me.

                            @{"Main Menu" link Main}

@Endnode

